        },
        {
            "text": "We es1mated significance for all four tests using 10,000 standard neutral coalescent simula1ons [9] . Because demography affects the SFS and can cause spurious results if not properly accounted for, our simula1ons are run under a demographic model which includes inferred parameters for popula1ons of African [10] , European [10] , Asian [10] and American [11] ancestry. In the case of the HKA we simulated demography since the split between chimp and humans using a divergence 1me of six million years ago. A custom made perl program (Neutrality Test Pipeline) was used to calculate the sta1s1c and its P--value.",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
